5 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
6 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 24-162 of Title 70, unless there
7 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
8 A. As used in this section:
9 1. “Antisemitism” has the same meaning as provided for by the
10 International Holocaust Remembrance Alliance Working Definition of
11 Antisemitism, including its contemporary examples, as it was adopted
12 on May 26, 2016;
13 2. “Institution of higher education” means an institution of
14 higher education within The Oklahoma State System of Higher
15 Education; and
16 3. “Public school” shall have the same meaning as provided for
17 in Section 1-106 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
18 B. Discrimination on the basis of race, ethnicity, national
19 origin, sex, disability, religion, or marital status against a
20 student or an employee in an institution of higher education or a
21 public school in this state shall be prohibited. No person in this
22 state shall, on the basis of race, ethnicity, national origin, sex,
23 disability, religion, or marital status, be excluded from
24 participating in, be denied the benefits of, or be subjected to
