18 students with limited proficiency in English, gifted students, or
19 students with disabilities or programs tailored to students with
20 specialized talents or skills.
21 E. Guidance, counseling, and financial assistance services in
22 institutions of higher education and public schools shall be
23 available to all students equally and provided in the same manner
